OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777449958
OL,3,CStarmer to face MPs after defeating
OL,4,Cbid to investigate claim he misled
OL,5,CCommons
OL,7,FThe weekly grilling is likely to see
OL,8,FSir Keir face further questions from
OL,9,Fthe Conservatives about Lord Peter
OL,10,FMandelson, following a day when Labour
OL,11,FMPs were whipped to oppose a Tory
OL,12,Fmotion calling for the Prime Minister
OL,13,Fto be investigated over his insistence
OL,14,Fthat due process was followed in the
OL,15,Fpeer's appointment as ambassador to
OL,16,Fthe US.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777449958
OL,3,CStarmer to face MPs after defeating
OL,4,Cbid to investigate claim he misled
OL,5,CCommons
OL,7,FThe motion from Conservative Party
OL,8,Fleader Kemi Badenoch would have seen
OL,9,FSir Keir referred to the Commons
OL,10,FPrivileges Committee in an echo of the
OL,11,Fprocess that eventually ended Boris
OL,12,FJohnson's political career.
OL,14,FMrs Badenoch has accused the Prime
OL,15,FMinister of misleading the Commons
OL,16,Fwhen he claimed due process was
OL,17,Ffollowed and no pressure was exerted
OL,18,Fto grant Lord Mandelson security
OL,19,Fclearance against official advice.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777449958
OL,3,CStarmer to face MPs after defeating
OL,4,Cbid to investigate claim he misled
OL,5,CCommons
OL,7,FBut despite a rebellion by 15
OL,8,Fbackbenchers, Labour MPs voted
OL,9,Fdecisively against launching an
OL,10,Finvestigation by a majority of 112 `
OL,11,Fslightly less than the Government's
OL,12,Fworking majority of 165.
OL,14,FFollowing the vote, Mrs Badenoch
OL,15,Faccused Labour MPs of being complicit
OL,16,Fin a "cover-up", saying they would
OL,17,F"rue the day" they voted against an
OL,18,Finquiry.
OL,26,@xD@FOUxD@OO]yD@AOUyD@MO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777449958
OL,3,CStarmer to face MPs after defeating
OL,4,Cbid to investigate claim he misled
OL,5,CCommons
OL,7,FDowning Street described the move as a
OL,8,F"desperate political stunt", adding
OL,9,Fthe Government would co-operate with
OL,10,Fexisting parliamentary inquiries into
OL,11,Fthe Mandelson affair.
OL,13,FOne of those inquiries took a step
OL,14,Fforward on Tuesday, with the
OL,15,Fannouncement that Parliament's
OL,16,FIntelligence and Security Committee
OL,17,F(ISC) had finished reviewing the
OL,18,FGovernment's requests to redact
OL,19,Fdocuments relating to the appointment
OL,20,Fbefore they are published in line with
OL,21,Fa demand from the Commons in February.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777449958
OL,3,CStarmer to face MPs after defeating
OL,4,Cbid to investigate claim he misled
OL,5,CCommons
OL,7,FThe Government could still challenge
OL,8,Fthose decisions at a private committee
OL,9,Fhearing, and it is unlikely that any
OL,10,Ffurther documents will be published
OL,11,Fbefore Parliament is prorogued on
OL,12,FWednesday.
OL,14,FISC chairman Lord Beamish said the
OL,15,Fcommittee had "made exceptional
OL,16,Fefforts to ensure that it is not
OL,17,Fholding up the publication of
OL,18,Fdocuments" and any delay in
OL,19,Fpublication of the documents was "in
OL,20,Fno way due to the committee's part in
OL,21,Fthe process".
OL,26,@wD@OOUzD@JO]{D@bOU}D@LO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777449958
OL,3,CStarmer to face MPs after defeating
OL,4,Cbid to investigate claim he misled
OL,5,CCommons
OL,7,FThe Prime Minister has consistently
OL,8,Fdenied misleading the House, leaning
OL,9,Fon the conclusion of former cabinet
OL,10,Fsecretary Sir Chris Wormald that
OL,11,F"appropriate processes" were followed.
OL,13,FBut earlier on Tuesday, former senior
OL,14,FForeign Office mandarin Sir Philip
OL,15,FBarton declined to endorse Sir Keir's
OL,16,Fassessment, saying it was for MPs to
OL,17,Fform their own view.
OL,26,@sD@AOUsD@WO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777449958
OL,3,CStarmer to face MPs after defeating
OL,4,Cbid to investigate claim he misled
OL,5,CCommons
OL,7,FSir Philip told the Commons Foreign
OL,8,FAffairs Committee it was unusual for
OL,9,Fthe peer's appointment to be announced
OL,10,Fbefore security vetting had been
OL,11,Fcompleted and suggested there was
OL,12,Fpressure to "get on with" approving
OL,13,FLord Mandelson's developed vetting
OL,14,F(DV).
OL,26,@tD@MOUtD@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/9
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
