CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1777449958
OL,3,CStarmer to face MPs after defeating
OL,4,Cbid to investigate claim he misled
OL,5,CCommons
OL,7,FThe committee also heard from Sir
OL,8,FKeir's former chief of staff Morgan
OL,9,FMcSweeney, who insisted he did not
OL,10,F"ask officials to ignore procedures,
OL,11,Frequest that steps should be skipped,
OL,12,For communicate explicitly or
OL,13,Fimplicitly that checks should be
OL,14,Fcleared at all costs" during the
OL,15,Fappointment of Lord Mandelson.
OL,26,@rD@AOUvD@UO]
